The paper presents a novel approach for multi-task learning with neural sequence models, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) research. The proposed method is based on graph neural networks, which are widely used in various subfields of computer science, including computer vision (CV), natural language processing (NLP), and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
